## TypeScript Strict Typing

### Configuration Requirements
```json
// tsconfig.json — Required settings
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "strict": true,
    "noImplicitAny": true,
    "noImplicitReturns": true,
    "noUncheckedIndexedAccess": true,
    "exactOptionalPropertyTypes": true
  }
}
```

### Interface Standards

```typescript
// REQUIRED: Exhaustive discriminated unions for API responses
type BriefingStatus = 'success' | 'failure' | 'degraded';

interface BriefingResponse {
  readonly status: BriefingStatus;
  readonly briefing: string;
  readonly metadata: ExecutionMetadata;
  readonly escalation?: EscalationPayload;
}

// REQUIRED: Zod schemas for runtime validation
import { z } from 'zod';

const briefingResponseSchema = z.object({
  status: z.enum(['success', 'failure', 'degraded']),
  briefing: z.string(),
  metadata: executionMetadataSchema,
  escalation: escalationPayloadSchema.optional(),
});

type BriefingResponse = z.infer<typeof briefingResponseSchema>;
```

